Needs — combined monorepo
=========================

This repository combines two upstream projects:

1. WeCode (https://github.com/duxweb/wecode) — Rust + GPUI desktop AI coding
   terminal, originally licensed under GPL-3.0. Its code lives in apps/ and
   crates/ (except crates/wecode-gateway).

2. Kiro Gateway (https://github.com/jwadow/kiro-gateway) — Python/FastAPI
   proxy gateway for the Kiro API (Amazon Q Developer / AWS CodeWhisperer),
   licensed under AGPL-3.0. It is being rewritten in Rust as
   crates/wecode-gateway; the original Python source is vendored read-only
   under reference/kiro-gateway/ for behavioral parity during the port and
   will be removed once parity is reached.

Because the gateway rewrite is a derivative work of AGPL-3.0 code, the
combined work in this repository is distributed under the terms of the
GNU Affero General Public License v3.0 (see LICENSE). GPL-3.0-licensed
WeCode code is combined with AGPL-3.0 code as permitted by GPLv3 §13;
per-crate `license` fields remain accurate for each component's origin.
